<div class="container py-4">
    <div class="row mb-4">
        <div class="col-12">
            <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded shadow">
                <div class="container">
                    <h2><i class="fas fa-compass"></i> How to Take a Survey</h2>
                
                    <div class="step">
                        <h3>Step 1: Access the Survey Link</h3>
                        <p>You receive an email or find a link on a website directing you to the survey. With one click, you open the survey page. It’s as easy as walking through an open door.</p>
                        <img src="your-image-url-1.jpg" alt="Start Survey">
                    </div>
                
                    <div class="step">
                        <h3>Step 2: Enter Your Details</h3>
                        <p>After clicking the link, the first page asks for basic information like your name, email, and perhaps a reference number. Just type in your details, ensuring everything is correct before moving on.</p>
                        <p><strong>Tip:</strong> Some surveys allow you to remain anonymous, so check for this option if you prefer.</p>
                        <img src="your-image-url-2.jpg" alt="Enter Details">
                    </div>
                
                    <div class="step">
                        <h3>Step 3: Begin Answering Questions</h3>
                        <p>Now, the heart of the survey begins. You’re presented with multiple-choice questions, rating scales, or text boxes where you can share your honest opinions.</p>
                        <img src="your-image-url-3.jpg" alt="Answering Questions">
                    </div>
                
                    <div class="step">
                        <h3>Step 4: Upload an Image (If Required)</h3>
                        <p>Some surveys may ask you to upload a photo. Click the "Upload" button, browse your files, and select the correct image. Once uploaded, the image preview appears.</p>
                        <p><strong>Tip:</strong> Make sure your image is clear and meets any size or format requirements.</p>
                        <img src="your-image-url-4.jpg" alt="Upload Image">
                    </div>
                
                    <div class="step">
                        <h3>Step 5: Review and Submit</h3>
                        <p>Before you finish, the survey often offers a summary page where you can review all your answers. Double-check for any errors or missing responses, then hit <strong>Submit</strong>.</p>
                        <img src="your-image-url-5.jpg" alt="Review and Submit">
                    </div>
                
                    <div class="step">
                        <h3>Step 6: Confirmation Message</h3>
                        <p>Once submitted, you’ll see a thank-you message confirming that your responses have been successfully recorded. Some surveys may even give you a follow-up or a chance to see the results.</p>
                        <img src="your-image-url-6.jpg" alt="Thank You Message">
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>